news.title: Thailand to offer land ownership to lure wealthy foreigners
news.para: Thailand has for decades been a popular expatriate destination for investment, retirement and for starting small businesses, but foreign land ownership has been restricted.

news.title: Supertech puts on sale two hotels, two malls to raise Rs 1,000 crore for completing projects
news.para: In a statement, Noida-based Supertech Ltd said that the company has put its assets -- shopping malls and hotels -- in Meerut and Haridwar on sale with the "target of raising funds to the tune of Rs 1,000 crore."

news.title: CIDCO puts 16 Navi Mumbai land parcels on the block, likely to fetch nearly Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: CIDCO has put a total 16 land parcels in prime locations of Navi Mumbai on the block. The proposed auction of land parcels spread over a total 12 acres is expected to generate revenue of nearly Rs 1,000 crore, said property consultants and developers operating in the satellite city of Mumbai.

news.title: Gurugram: Shops, dhabas on residential plots demolished in DLF-2
news.para: The team has recommended registering FIR against the property owners under the provisions of Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Act 1975.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to auction Rs 1,200 crore land for SCOs
news.para: Along with commercial area which will have SCOs, the UT administration will also develop banquet hall and green belts for the utilisation of 25 acre land in Sector 52 and 56, worth Rs 1,200 crore.

news.title: Over 190 residents in Jaipur get land deeds
news.para: In JMC-Heritage areas, 168 deeds were given to residents. In JMC-Greater, 24 land deeds were given along with transfer of names for eight people, and subdivision letters were handed over to five residents.

news.title: Lucknow: Now, register and self assess to pay your property tax online
news.para: Mayor said “This is a very good initiative to fight corruption. We bring this platform so that everyone is able to register his/her house easily. In case of any glitches or problems we will rectify it accordingly.”

news.title: Chandigarh civic body takes possession of Rs 350 crore Manimajra land
news.para: A team of MC officers resumed this prime land in pocket No 9, Manimajra adjoining Indra Colony Green Belt and opposite Manimajra police station. The land is in three parts, 6.90 acres, 4.54 acres and 1.04 acres.

news.title: Kolkata: Move to launch unit area assessment in Sector V
news.para: ​The West Bengal Valuation Board has come up with a proposed draft scheme on the UAA system of tax collection for Sector V, which the Nabadiganta Industrial Township Authority (NDITA) expects to be finalised for introduction from the next financial year.

news.title: Rajasthan CM announces special drive for issuing land deeds
news.para: Officials have been directed to reach out to the doorsteps of families/households who have not applied for their land deeds. The announcement was made during the review meeting of the campaign with DMs at his residence here on Thursday.

news.title: HSVP cancels Kingdom of Dreams' land lease over Rs 208 crore dues
news.para: Officials said while KOD had defaulted on paying Rs 108 crore in rent, HSVP had imposed a penalty of Rs 100 crore on it. Sources in the agency said HSVP might auction the property in future.

news.title: Happiest Minds buys 2.4 lakh sq ft office space for Rs 101 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: The facility with a seating capacity of 1,600 seats is in the technology hub of Electronics City.

news.title: Vedanta chairman's family buys sea-view apartment in Mumbai for Rs 45 crore
news.para: The sea-view apartment on the 36th floor of the super-structure has been acquired by Agarwal’s wife Kiran, who is chairman of Hindustan Zinc and a trustee of Vedanta Foundation.

news.title: Oberoi Realty posts net profit of Rs 403.08 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 934.81 crore in Q1 FY23, a growth of 217 per cent from Rs 294.77 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bombay HC raps government for stalling demolition of illegal buildings
news.para: The court was hearing a PIL filed in 2021 by three persons on the issue of the April 2014 collapse of a building in Lucky Compound in Mumbra that killed some 80 people.
